      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>The following reaction, called the <i>benzilic acid rearrangement,</i> takes place by typical carbonyl-group reactions. Propose a mechanism (Ph = phenyl).</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBaTBYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--6cb4e623429132a0ff5d75c8099ba9a8697e094e/OChem_21_EC_037.jpg\" alt=\"Benzil is converted to a benzylic acid by treatment first with aqueous sodium hydroxide and then with acid. Benzil is a dicarbonyl compound with two carbonyl groups joined to one another and a benzene ring on each carbonyl. The reaction occurs by a rearrangement.\">",
